MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d0a663575cba5a64886a6bdb08734bb7, type: 3}
  m_Name: OpeningDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueNode
  speakerName: Whim
  lines:
  - "You fall into a dream, gently. It\u2019s softer than everything else you\u2019ve
    experienced today, in this life, in this horrid forest. You float in an endless
    world of vibrant colors slowly shifting, amorphous, touching to create new colors\u2026"
  - A hand takes your arm and pulls you down, backward, through a wood-paneled door,
    onto a wooden floor. The door shutting before you. You mourn the tranquility
    you had before this interruption.
  - "\u201CHello!\u201D"
  - "You\u2019ve never heard speech before, but you understand it. That fact is almost
    frightening."
  - "\u201CHello?\u201D"
  - "The young woman sounds more disappointed than concerned when you don\u2019t
    respond. Then, something tiny and bright and colorful whips around you, coming
    to a halt directly in your eyeline."
  - "It\u2019s a creature. It\u2019s something like you; upright with legs and arms.
    The unfathomable part of your mind that somehow understands all of this feeds
    you the words: person, Pixie. It\u2019s a Pixie. She\u2019s a Pixie."
  - "\u201CI thought you\u2019d be able to understand me\u2026\u201D"
  - '> Respond'
  - You make a noise, attempting speech for the first time. It comes out broken,
    not like anything, but she seems to understand that, at the very least, you were
    trying to prove her correct.
  - "\u201COh~! Wonderful! This is incredibly fortunate, you know. It\u2019s a miracle
    one of my old projects survived in there.\u201D Her giggle is unsettling after
    those words. You try to put together the implications, but she interrupts you
    again quickly."
  - "\u201CYou\u2019re in trouble. You probably can\u2019t tell yet, but you\u2019ve
    been infected. There\u2019s a fungus growing in your head\u2014\u201D She flutters
    closer and pokes your forehead. \u201C\u2014and soon enough it\u2019ll turn you
    into another monster roaming the swamp. You don\u2019t want that, do you?\u201D"
  - '> No'
  - You find it easier to shake your head.
  - "\u201CGood. Then listen carefully. Also\u2026\u201D "
  - "She gestures to the air, and a few seconds later, something rectangular flies
    to her open arms. She places it in your hands. It\u2019s a book. "
  - "\u201CHold this. Now, you don\u2019t have a lot of time. You need to assemble
    a ritual to fix yourself. It will need a magic circle and an incantation\u2026
    and probably some materials too. I can only do so much from out here, but I will
    help. For a favor, of course, but I have a feeling you\u2019d do what I want
    anyways, once you\u2019re safe, yourself. Now\u2026\u201D "
  - 'She flutters to the side, and the door opens to the colorful void. Tendrils
    of desaturation encroach upon it already. '
  - "\u201CGet up and get going!\u201D You are thrust out of the door, tumbling in
    vibrant space until you awake, dizzy, on the forest floor, that book in your
    arms."
  triggerKey: Intro
  nextNode: {fileID: 0}
  onComplete:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  typingSpeed: 0.05
  autoProgressDelay: 1.5
